.TH "scsi_eh_bus_device_reset" 9 "scsi_eh_bus_device_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_eh_bus_device_reset \- send bdr if needed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_eh_bus_device_reset
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ","
.BI "struct list_head *work_q "  ","
.BI "struct list_head *done_q "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shost" 12
scsi host being recovered.
.IP "work_q" 12
\fIlist_head\fP for pending commands.
.IP "done_q" 12
\fIlist_head\fP for processed commands.
.SH "NOTES"
Try a bus device reset.  Still, look to see whether we have multiple
devices that are jammed or not - if we have multiple devices, it
makes no sense to try bus_device_reset - we really would need to try
a bus_reset instead.
